  "abstract": "Investments in health care facilities, diagnostic and therapeutic equipment, and information and communications technology, affect the capacity to respond to population needs. There are no guidelines or international benchmarks regarding the optimal level of capital investment in the health sector. Nonetheless, it is of critical importance for countries to maintain spare capacity to deal with surges â€“ too little investment will over-stretch service provision, undermining health system resilience.",
